---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = '10 June 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy — Dokkimi"
  description="How Dokkimi uses cookies, what we collect, and how to manage your consent."
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="container policy">
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

    <p>
      This policy explains how Dokkimi uses cookies and similar technologies on
      <a href="https://dokkimi.com">dokkimi.com</a>, what each cookie does, and how you
      can control them. We keep this deliberately simple: we use cookies only for privacy-
      respecting analytics, and we do not set any analytics cookies until you opt in.
    </p>

    <h2>What cookies are</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small text files a website stores in your browser. Some are required for
      the site to function; others help us understand how the site is used so we can improve
      it. You are always in control of the optional ones.
    </p>

    <h2>How we use them</h2>
    <p>
      We use one category of optional cookies — <strong>analytics</strong> — provided by
      Google Analytics 4, loaded through Google Tag Manager. These cookies are set
      <strong>only after you click “Accept”</strong> on our cookie banner. If you decline, or
      ignore the banner, no analytics cookies are stored and no analytics data is collected.
      We do not use advertising cookies, and we do not sell or share your personal
      information.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies we may set</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Cookie</th><th>Category</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Typical duration</th><th>Provider</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>cc_cookie</code></td>
            <td>Necessary</td>
            <td>Stores your cookie consent choice so we don’t ask again on every visit.</td>
            <td>6 months</td>
            <td>Dokkimi (first-party)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>_ga</code></td>
            <td>Analytics</td>
            <td>Distinguishes individual visitors to measure site usage.</td>
            <td>Up to 2 years</td>
            <td>Google Analytics</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>_ga_&lt;id&gt;</code></td>
            <td>Analytics</td>
            <td>Maintains Google Analytics 4 session state.</td>
            <td>Up to 2 years</td>
            <td>Google Analytics</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>_gid</code></td>
            <td>Analytics</td>
            <td>Distinguishes visitors (set by Google Analytics in some configurations).</td>
            <td>24 hours</td>
            <td>Google Analytics</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="note">
      Durations for the Google cookies are set by Google and may change; the values above
      reflect Google’s published defaults at the time of writing.
    </p>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <p>
      Analytics data is processed by Google as our data processor. For details on how Google
      uses this data, see
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/cookies" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google’s cookie information</a>.
      We have enabled Consent Mode v2, which means Google’s tags respect your consent choice
      and do not store analytics cookies or collect analytics data until you opt in.
    </p>

    <h2>Managing your consent</h2>
    <p>
      You can change or withdraw your choice at any time using the button below, or by clearing
      cookies in your browser settings.
    </p>
    <button type="button" class="manage-btn" data-cc="show-preferencesModal">
      Manage cookie preferences
    </button>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy? Email
      <a href="mailto:hello@dokkimi.com">hello@dokkimi.com</a>.
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .policy {
    padding: 140px 0 var(--section-spacing);
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .policy h1 {
    font-size: 2.4rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .updated {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .policy h2 {
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 40px 0 12px;
  }

  .policy p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .policy strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 8px 0 12px;
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  th,
  td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 10px 12px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    vertical-align: top;
  }

  th {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  td {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .note {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .manage-btn {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: 12px 24px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--color-primary-soft);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .manage-btn:hover {
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-bg);
  }
</style>
